File: Lightbulb Unsplash/Johannes Plenio JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will be implementing load reduction in areas of the Free State, Gauteng, Limpopo and KwaZulu-Natal. The load reduction will take place between 5 pm and 10 pm on Thursday. READ: Eskom: Load-shedding here to stay In Gauteng, customers in the Katlehong, Vosloorus will be affected. In the Free State, Thabo Mofutsanyana District will be experiencing load reduction. KwaZulu-Natal and Limpopo will also be experiencing power cuts.